nd locale-specific separators (e.g., European `1.234,56`). The transformation will involve stripping non-numeric characters (except for the decimal separator), handling thousand separators (e.g., removing dots), swapping comma to decimal point if present, and then casting to `DOUBLE PRECISION`.\n\n## NOT NULL Constraints and Default Values\nAll `NOT NULL` target columns will be populated to satisfy their constraints. If a source column is `NULL` or unparseable for a `NOT NULL` target column, a meaningful default value will be provided (e.g., 'Unknown Account', '1900-01-01', or a default enum value).\n\n## Standard System Fields\n`CreatedDate` and `LastModifiedDate` will be populated with the current timestamp in `YYYY-MM-DD HH24:MI:SS` text format. `IsDeleted` will be defaulted to `0`.\n\nThe SQL statement transforms master_kunden into the Account target schema. It handles NOT NULL constraints for 'Name' with COALESCE and maps 'kundenklasse' to 'Customer_Tier__c' using a CASE statement for enum validation. System fields like CreatedDate, LastModifiedDate, and IsDeleted are populated with current timestamps or a default value respectively."
